	"summary": {
		"english": "In this lesson, you learned how to greet people using 'Ahlan' and 'Ezzayak', how to introduce yourself with 'Ana' and 'Ismy', and how to politely end a conversation with 'Ma'a el salama'.",
		"arabic": "في الدرس ده اتعلمت إزاي تسلم باستخدام 'أهلاً' و'إزيك'، وإزاي تعرف نفسك بـ 'أنا' و'إسمي'، وإزاي تنهي الكلام بأدب بـ 'مع السلامة'."
	},
	"keyTakeaways": [
		"Egyptians use 'Ezzayak' (m) and 'Ezzayek' (f) to ask 'How are you'.",
		"The standard reply to 'How are you' is almost always 'El hamdu lellah' (Thank God).",
		"To say 'My name is...', say 'Ismy...'.",
		"Question words like 'Eh' (What) usually come at the end of the sentence."
	],
	"grammarFocus": [
